<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Philippines     06-18 0204</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Philippines,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Human Rights Lawyer Shot Dead Near U.S. Base</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANGELES, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A human rights lawyer who
represented a top Communist Party official was assasinated today as
he swept his front yard near the U.S. Clark Air Base, police said.
   Police said gunmen casually approached Ramos Cura, 44, as he
worked in his front yard and shot him several times. The assailants
fled on foot.
   Cura was the 27th person killed in this city since last month
and the seventh in June, police records show. Most of the killings
have remained unsolved and residents have complained about the rash
of violence in Angeles, home of the U.S. 13th Air Force.
   The victim was a lawyer of jailed communist leader Rodolfo
Salas, allegedly a former chairman of the Communist Party of the
Philippines which has waged a 19-year insurgency against the
government.
   Cura was also the secretary of the Pampanga provincial chapter
of the leftwing nationalist organization BAYAN.
   Police said they had no suspects on the killing.
   In a related development, suspected communist rebels ambushed
and killed constabulary Sgt. Arcadio Dizon late Friday in
neighboring Tarlac province. A militiaman on board the same jeep
with Sgt. Dizon escaped unhurt, the military reported.
</TEXT>
