<HEAD>Gulf Air Carriers in Joint Venture for Islamic Flight Kitchen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUWAIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The national airlines of three Arab states are
working out a joint venture agreement with the Marriott Corp. to
set up an Islamic flight kitchen at London's Heathrow airport, an
official said Saturday.
   ``It is anticipated that the agreement will be initiated within
the next four to six weeks with a formal signing ceremony scheduled
for mid-September,'' Ahmed Mishari, chairman of the Kuwait Airways
Corporation, told the Associated Press.
