<2ND_LINE>AM-Warrant-Excerpts,500</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With AM-Defense Probe Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are excerpts from the four-page search
warrant signed last Monday by U.S. District Judge John H. Pratt.
The FBI obtained the warrant to seize materials from the office of
Eugene Tallia, vice president of Pratt & Whitney and head of the
company's Washington office. The offices were searched Tuesday but
it is not known what was found.
   A copy of the warrant was obtained by the trade paper Defense
Week and made available Saturday to The Associated Press.
   
   TO: D. Strebel Pierce and any authorized officer of the United
States. ...I am satisfied that the affidavit(s) and any recorded
testimony establish probable cause to believe that the property so
described is now concealed on the person or premises
above-described and establish grounds for the issuance of this
warrant.
   You are hereby commanded to search on or before 10 days from
date of warrant. ...
   Signed by U.S. District Judge John H. Pratt...
   
   Description of property to be seized:
   1. Copies of General Electric's proposals to the government on
the 404 and JVX (an experimental project) projects or any other
documents containing information which should not have been
released from the government.
   2. Statements of work, proposals, agreements, purchase orders,
invoices, bills, correspondence, memoranda, notes and other
documents relating to Pratt & Whitney employment of William Galvin,
Melvyn Paisley and-or their corporations.
   3. Eugene Tallia's appointment books and calendar for 1985,
1986, 1987 and 1988 showing meetings and other events relating to
Paisley, Galvin and-or the JVX and 404 projects.
   4. Notes, memoranda, correspondence, Rolodex, reports and other
documents relating to the agreements, conservations or other
contracts between Pratt & Whitney and its employees and Galvin and
Paisley or their corporations.
   5. Notes, memoranda, correspondence and other documents
relationg to Pratt & Whitney's proposal to the government on the
404 and JVX projects and-or contacts betweeen Pratt & Whitney's
employees and United States government employees on those projects.
   6. Statements of work, agreements, purchase orders, invoices,
bills notes, memoranda, correspondence, notes and other documents
relating to Pratt & Whitney's second source agreement on the JVX
and-or contacts between Pratt & Whitney's employees, ... or United
States government employees on that project.
   7. Copies of Pratt & Whitney's proposals to the government on
the 404 project.
   8. Copies of Pratt & Whitney's prooposal to the government on
the JVX project.
   9. Copies of Pratt & Whitney's proposal to ... the government on
the second source agreement for the JVX project.
   10. Computer storage devices containing records, documents and
information described above in paragraphs 1 thru 9, and related
computer equipment and materials for adequately retrieving and
reviewing the information, including magnetic tapes, magnetic
disks, punch cards, paper tapes, optical disk storage media,
central processing units, printers, terminal display screens,
optical disk drives, magnetic tape drives, magnetic disk drives and
instruction manuals.
</TEXT>
