<2ND_LINE>AM-Gang Violence,0256</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Killed, Eight Hurt in Separate Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Armed gang members shot up a
graduation party, wounding five teen-agers, and one man was slain
in gang violence elsewhere in the Los Angeles area, police said
Saturday.
   Six alleged gang members were arrested after shots were fired
into a car in Hollywood, authorities said.
   Growing gang violence in Los Angeles and parts of Los Angeles
County has led police to conduct weekend-long sweeps that have
resulted in hundreds of arrests.
   Teen-agers at a dance in a garage in this southern Los Angeles
County community were attacked late Friday, Lt. Rob Mickelson said.
   Two men apparently went into the party and got into an argument
that ended with the shooting, he said. Two boys, ages 17 and 15,
and three 17-year-old girls suffered minor wounds, he said.
   A description of the getaway car led to two arrests, and an
AK-47 rifle and a semi-automatic handgun were seized, he said.
   A Los Angeles man was shot to death and another wounded early
Saturday in a gang-related attack at a dance attended by rival
gangs in the county's Vermont area, said sheriff's Deputy Roxanna
Schuchman.
   A fight had broken out outside a social club between two men,
one of whom pulled a gun and fired several shots, Ms. Schuchman
said.
   Six alleged gang members were arrested in Hollywood early
Saturday after they allegedly fired five shots into a car, whose
occupant was unhurt, police said.
