<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Whale Death,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Baby Whale Found on Beach Dies at Sea World</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A newborn pygmy sperm whale that beached
itself near Patrick Air Force Base died Friday at Sea World marine
park in Orlando, park officials said.
   The 2-foot calf, orphaned when its mother died in the surf, had
been cared for by animal handlers at Sea World since late Tuesday.
But they had not expected him to survive since most whales only
seek land when they are in extreme difficulty.
   The animal apparently died from a combination of factors, said
Sea World research biologist Dan Odell. The results of a necropsy
to determine the cause of death are not expected for several weeks,
he said.
   The cause of death of the 10-foot mother whale also has not been
determined.
</TEXT>
