<1ST_LINE>r p PM-Politics-Quotes     06-18 0166</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Politics-Quotes,200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From The Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, responding to attacks by Sen. John McCain,
R-Ariz., levelled from Tennessee and Florida that Dukakis is a
``Teddy Kennedy liberal'' who is soft on crime: ``They send some
guy from Arizona to Florida who doesn't know beans from brown
bread.''
   
   SEN. SAM NUNN of Georgia, asked if he would accept a spot on the
presidential ticket with Dukakis if invited: ``I think it's very
presumptuous to sort of set up a hypothetical example of what one
would do if one were offered something that one is not seeking and
one is discouraging.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, on allegations of widespread bribery and corruption
at the Pentagon: ``Corruption anywhere in government is bad enough,
but these people, should the allegations prove true, were not just
stealing money from the Treasury, they were stealing from our
national defense and undermining our national security.''
